Here is the cleaned up text:

Your network of agents and brokers who sell your insurance products need access to specific features and functions to service their accounts. The Broker Experience site on the Experience Cloud can give them that access.

To use the Broker Experience template, you must install the Insurance FSC Unmanaged Package.

You can brand the components with your colors, fonts, logo, and other styles. You can also customize the substance of the components by adding or removing data, changing the data source, adding new elements, and more.

What Agents and Brokers Can Do in the Broker Site

When a broker logs in to the site, they see the Home Page. Out of the box, the Home page looks like this:

Brokers can do the following things on this page:

* See a list of recent quotes
* Sort and filter the list of quotes
* Click any quote name to see its details

The Quote detail page looks like this:

Brokers can do the following things on this page:

* View the root insurance product for the quote (and any coverages attached to it)
* View and edit the insured items on the quote
* View and edit quote details
* View and edit related records attached to this quote
* View documents attached to the quote
* Do any actions available in the Action panel

Manage Accounts

A broker can click the Account tab to see and manage their accounts.

Create, Update, and Manage Quotes

A broker can click the Quotes tab to see a list of quotes, go to quote details, create new quotes, update and manage existing quotes, and issue policies.

Manage Existing Policies

A broker can click the Policies tab to view, update, and manage existing policies.

Broker Experience Template

This template includes standard Salesforce Experience components and custom-built Vlocity Insurance components.
